    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-06-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-06-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="441"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d441">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/13205: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief of the United States Asiatic Fleet</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Yarnell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Commander of the Yangtze Patrol</hi>
                        (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Le Breton</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="52a" xml:id="d441fn52a">Copy transmitted to the Department
                        of State by the Navy Department on June 13, 1938.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-13">June 13,
                            1938</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>0012. In connection my despatch of 12th to Ambassador, it is not intended that
                    United States ships shall remain within area of active military engagements.
                    After full opportunity has been offered for evacuation of nationals, notice of
                    probable date of withdrawal of gunboats from a specific area should be given.
                    These dates will normally be left to your discretion. 1335.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
